President Biden gave a speech at the 30th Street Station in Philadelphia to celebrate Amtrak's 50th anniversary. He expressed his personal connection to Amtrak, having taken thousands of trips on the train throughout his career. He emphasized the importance of investing in rail infrastructure, both for economic and environmental reasons. Biden highlighted the potential for job creation and expanded rail service, envisioning faster and more reliable transportation options between cities. He also mentioned the need to compete with other countries, such as China, that have extensive high-speed rail networks. Biden concluded by expressing his optimism for the future of Amtrak and rail transportation in the United States.